A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
AN ACT
1 To amend Code Section 19-6-15 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to child
2 support guidelines for determining amount of award, continuation of duty of support, and
3 duration of support, so as to provide for the duration of child support for postsecondary
4 education; to provide for related matters; to provide for an effective date and applicability;
5 to repeal conflicting laws; and for other purposes.
6 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF GEORGIA:
7 SECTION 1.
8 Code Section 19-6-15 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to child support
9 guidelines for determining amount of award, continuation of duty of support, and duration
10 of support, is amended by revising subsection (e) as follows:
11 "(e)(1) Duration of child support responsibility. The duty to provide support for a
12 minor child shall continue until the child reaches the age of majority, dies, marries, or
13 becomes emancipated, whichever first occurs; provided, however, that, in any temporary,
14 final, or modified order for child support with respect to any proceeding for divorce,
15 separate maintenance, legitimacy, or paternity entered on or after July 1, 1992, the court,
16 in the exercise of sound discretion, may direct either or both parents to provide financial
