17 assistance to a child who has not previously married or become emancipated, who is
18 enrolled in and attending a secondary school, and who has attained the age of majority
19 before completing his or her secondary school education, provided that such financial
20 assistance shall not be required after a child attains 20 years of age. The provisions for
21 child support provided in this subsection paragraph may be enforced by either parent, by
22 any nonparent custodian, by a guardian appointed to receive child support for the child
23 for whose benefit the child support is ordered, or by the child for whose benefit the child
24 support is ordered.
25 (2) Duration of child support for postsecondary education. In any temporary, final,
26 or modified order for child support with respect to any proceeding for divorce, separate
27 maintenance, legitimacy, or paternity entered on or after July 1, 2025, the court, in the
28 exercise of sound discretion, may direct either or both parents to provide financial
29 assistance to a child who is enrolled in and attending a technical school, vocational
30 school, college, university, or other institution of postsecondary education, provided that
31 such financial assistance shall not be required after a child attains 24 years of age. The
32 court shall require verification of such enrollment and attendance. In determining the
33 amount of such financial assistance, the court shall consider the amount of tuition as well
34 as additional fees and expenses related to such enrollment and attendance. The
35 provisions for child support provided in this paragraph may be enforced by either parent,
36 by any nonparent custodian, by a guardian appointed to receive child support for the child
37 for whose benefit the child support is ordered, or by the child for whose benefit the child
38 support is ordered."
39 SECTION 2.
40 This Act shall become effective on July 1, 2025, and shall apply to all support orders entered
41 on or after such date.
